'''Barra''' is a minor character in ''Game of Thrones''. The young actor or actress playing her has not been identified. She only appears in the [[The Wolf and the Lion|fifth episode]] of the [[Season 1|first season]] and the [[The North Remembers|first episode]] of the [[Season 2|second season]]. She is the [[bastard]] child of King [[Robert Baratheon]] and [[Mhaegen]].

sections.Biography:
===Background===
Barra is an infant, the bastard child of King [[Robert Baratheon]] and [[Mhaegen]]. Mhaeghen is a prostitute working for [[Petyr Baelish]] in [[King's Landing]]. Barra lives with Mhaegen in one of his brothels. Her name may be a reference to her father's noble House, Baratheon.

===[[Season 1]]===
[[Petyr Baelish|Lord Baelish]] brings [[Eddard Stark]] to see [[Mhaegen]] at his brothel. She tells him that her daughter Barra is [[Robert Baratheon]]'s child, one of his many bastards. [[Jaime Lannister]] and his men ambush Eddard while he is leaving the brothel where Barra lives.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Wolf and the Lion]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 2]]===
During a [[Massacre in King's Landing|purge]] of the late King Robert's bastard children carried out by the [[City Watch|Gold Cloaks]], Barra is killed by Lord [[Janos Slynt]] before the eyes of her mother and several prostitutes, including [[Ros]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The North Remembers]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
